  "texts": [
    "As pointed out by one of the anonymous reviewers, focusing on abductive reasoning and explanatory process also has one particular advantage over a more standard approach.",
    "In xAI, a causal explanation is usually pursued as the desired result of the xAI methods.",
    "It makes sense to desire to have an account of what particular cause led to the event.",
    "However, causal explanation is very demanding, especially in the face of incomplete evidence (which is usually the case in healthcare contexts).",
    "So often, the best we can do is to guess (cf.Popper, 1959, p. 278), which human reasoners often do."
  ],
